radiusAccServMIB.name: radiusAccServMIB

revisions.description: Revised version as published in RFC xxxx. This version obsoletes that of RFC 2621 by deprecating the MIB table containing IPv4-only address formats and defining a new table to add support for version neutral IP address formats. The remaining MIB objects from RFC 2621 are carried forward into this version.
Initial version as published in RFC 2621.

radiusAccServMIB.description: The MIB module for entities implementing the server side of the Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service (RADIUS) accounting protocol. Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2006). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC xxxx; see the RFC itself forfull legal notices.

radiusMIB.name: radiusMIB
radiusMIB.description: The OID assigned to RADIUS MIB work by the IANA.

radiusAccServIdent.name: radiusAccServIdent
radiusAccServIdent.description: The implementation identification string for the RADIUS accounting server software in use on the system, for example; `FNS-2.1'

radiusAccServUpTime.name: radiusAccServUpTime
radiusAccServUpTime.description: If the server has a persistent state (e.g., a process), this value will be the time elapsed (in hundredths of a second) since the server process was started. For software without persistent state, this value will be zero.

radiusAccServResetTime.name: radiusAccServResetTime
radiusAccServResetTime.description: If the server has a persistent state (e.g., a process) and supports a `reset' operation (e.g., can be told to re-read configuration files), this value will be the time elapsed (in hundredths of a second) since the server was `reset.' For software that does not have persistence or does not support a `reset' operation, this value will be zero.

radiusAccServConfigReset.name: radiusAccServConfigReset
radiusAccServConfigReset.description: Status/action object to reinitialize any persistent server state. When set to reset(2), any persistent server state (such as a process) is reinitialized as if the server had just been started. This value will never be returned by a read operation. When read, one of the following values will be returned: other(1) - server in some unknown state; initializing(3) - server (re)initializing; running(4) - server currently running.

radiusAccServTotalRequests.name: radiusAccServTotalRequests
radiusAccServTotalRequests.description: The number of packets received on the accounting port.

radiusAccServTotalInvalidRequests.name: radiusAccServTotalInvalidRequests
radiusAccServTotalInvalidRequests.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets received from unknown addresses.

radiusAccServTotalDupRequests.name: radiusAccServTotalDupRequests
radiusAccServTotalDupRequests.description: The number of duplicate RADIUS Accounting-Request packets received.

radiusAccServTotalResponses.name: radiusAccServTotalResponses
radiusAccServTotalResponses.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Response packets sent.

radiusAccServTotalMalformedRequests.name: radiusAccServTotalMalformedRequests
radiusAccServTotalMalformedRequests.description: The number of malformed RADIUS Accounting-Request packets received. Bad authenticators or unknown types are not included as malformed Access-Requests.

radiusAccServTotalBadAuthenticators.name: radiusAccServTotalBadAuthenticators
radiusAccServTotalBadAuthenticators.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which contained an invalid authenticator.

radiusAccServTotalPacketsDropped.name: radiusAccServTotalPacketsDropped
radiusAccServTotalPacketsDropped.description: The number of incoming packets silently discarded for a reason other than malformed, bad authenticators, or unknown types.

radiusAccServTotalNoRecords.name: radiusAccServTotalNoRecords
radiusAccServTotalNoRecords.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which were received and responded to but not recorded.

radiusAccServTotalUnknownTypes.name: radiusAccServTotalUnknownTypes
radiusAccServTotalUnknownTypes.description: The number of RADIUS packets of unknown type which were received.

radiusAccClientTable.name: radiusAccClientTable
radiusAccClientTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS accounting clients with which the server shares a secret.

radiusAccClientEntry.name: radiusAccClientEntry
radiusAccClientEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS accounting client with which the server shares a secret.

radiusAccClientIndex.name: radiusAccClientIndex
radiusAccClientIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each RADIUS accounting client with which this server communicates.

radiusAccClientAddress.name: radiusAccClientAddress
radiusAccClientAddress.description: The NAS-IP-Address of the RADIUS accounting client referred to in this table entry.

radiusAccClientID.name: radiusAccClientID
radiusAccClientID.description: The NAS-Identifier of the RADIUS accounting client referred to in this table entry. This is not necessarily the same as sysName in MIB II.

radiusAccServPacketsDropped.name: radiusAccServPacketsDropped
radiusAccServPacketsDropped.description: The number of incoming packets received from this client and silently discarded for a reason other than malformed, bad authenticators, or unknown types.

radiusAccServRequests.name: radiusAccServRequests
radiusAccServRequests.description: The number of packets received from this client on the accounting port.

radiusAccServDupRequests.name: radiusAccServDupRequests
radiusAccServDupRequests.description: The number of duplicate RADIUS Accounting-Request packets received from this client.

radiusAccServResponses.name: radiusAccServResponses
radiusAccServResponses.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Response packets sent to this client.

radiusAccServBadAuthenticators.name: radiusAccServBadAuthenticators
radiusAccServBadAuthenticators.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which contained invalid authenticators received from this client.

radiusAccServMalformedRequests.name: radiusAccServMalformedRequests
radiusAccServMalformedRequests.description: The number of malformed RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which were received from this client. Bad authenticators and unknown types are not included as malformed Accounting-Requests.

radiusAccServNoRecords.name: radiusAccServNoRecords
radiusAccServNoRecords.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which were received and responded to but not recorded.

radiusAccServUnknownTypes.name: radiusAccServUnknownTypes
radiusAccServUnknownTypes.description: The number of RADIUS packets of unknown type which were received from this client.

radiusAccClientExtTable.name: radiusAccClientExtTable
radiusAccClientExtTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS accounting clients with which the server shares a secret.

radiusAccClientExtEntry.name: radiusAccClientExtEntry
radiusAccClientExtEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS accounting client with which the server shares a secret.

radiusAccClientExtIndex.name: radiusAccClientExtIndex
radiusAccClientExtIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each RADIUS accounting client with which this server communicates.

radiusAccClientInetAddressType.name: radiusAccClientInetAddressType
radiusAccClientInetAddressType.description: The type of address format used for the radiusAccClientInetAddress object.

radiusAccClientInetAddress.name: radiusAccClientInetAddress
radiusAccClientInetAddress.description: The IP address of the RADIUS accounting client referred to in this table entry, using the IPv6 address format.

radiusAccClientExtID.name: radiusAccClientExtID
radiusAccClientExtID.description: The NAS-Identifier of the RADIUS accounting client referred to in this table entry. This is not necessarily the same as sysName in MIB II.

radiusAccServExtPacketsDropped.name: radiusAccServExtPacketsDropped
radiusAccServExtPacketsDropped.description: The number of incoming packets received from this client and silently discarded for a reason other than malformed, bad authenticators, or unknown types. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServExtRequests.name: radiusAccServExtRequests
radiusAccServExtRequests.description: The number of packets received from this client on the accounting port. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServExtDupRequests.name: radiusAccServExtDupRequests
radiusAccServExtDupRequests.description: The number of duplicate RADIUS Accounting-Request packets received from this client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServExtResponses.name: radiusAccServExtResponses
radiusAccServExtResponses.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Response packets sent to this client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServExtBadAuthenticators.name: radiusAccServExtBadAuthenticators
radiusAccServExtBadAuthenticators.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which contained invalid authenticators received from this client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServExtMalformedRequests.name: radiusAccServExtMalformedRequests
radiusAccServExtMalformedRequests.description: The number of malformed RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which were received from this client. Bad authenticators and unknown types are not included as malformed Accounting-Requests. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServExtNoRecords.name: radiusAccServExtNoRecords
radiusAccServExtNoRecords.description: The number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets which were received and responded to but not recorded. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServExtUnknownTypes.name: radiusAccServExtUnknownTypes
radiusAccServExtUnknownTypes.description: The number of RADIUS packets of unknown type which were received from this client. This counter may experience a discontinuity when the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity is reinitialized, as indicated by the current value of radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.

radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.name: radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity
radiusAccServerCounterDiscontinuity.description: The number of centiseconds since the last discontinuity in the RADIUS Accounting Server counters. A discontinuity may be the result of a reinitialization of the RADIUS Accounting Server module within the managed entity.

radiusAccServMIBCompliance.name: radiusAccServMIBCompliance
radiusAccServMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for accounting servers implementing the RADIUS Accounting Server MIB. Implementation of this module is for IPv4-only entities, or for backwards compatibility use with entities that support both IPv4 and IPv6.

radiusAccServExtMIBCompliance.name: radiusAccServExtMIBCompliance
radiusAccServExtMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for accounting servers implementing the RADIUS Accounting Server IPv6 Extensions MIB. Implementation of this module is for entities that support IPv6, or support IPv4 and IPv6.

radiusAccServMIBGroup.name: radiusAccServMIBGroup
radiusAccServMIBGroup.description: The collection of objects providing management of a RADIUS Accounting Server.

radiusAccServExtMIBGroup.name: radiusAccServExtMIBGroup
radiusAccServExtMIBGroup.description: The collection of objects providing management of a RADIUS Accounting Server.
